title: Urbanization in Japan 2018
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Share of urban population. In total the number of data points it has is 11.
In general Share of urban population has stayed the same over the Year.
Share of urban population is slightly increasing from 2008 to 2010, and finally roughly constant from 2010 to 2018.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2008 and 2009.
Maximum Share of urban population, about 91.62 was reported at Year 2018
The lowest Share of urban population, of value 89.1 was reported at Year 2008
